  "executive_summary": "The migrated infrastructure consists of 20 AWS resources across 7 service categories. The architecture follows a standard multi-tier pattern with VPC isolation (public/private subnets), an EKS cluster for containerized workloads, RDS for relational persistence, ElastiCache for caching, and Lambda for serverless image processing. The estimated monthly AWS cost of $1,087.40 represents a 19.7% savings ($266.60/month) compared to the GCP equivalent at $1,354.00. Key improvements include KMS encryption on all storage, deletion protection on RDS, and upgraded instance types from deprecated N1 to M5/T3 families. The EKS cluster with 3 m5.xlarge nodes accounts for the largest cost component at $493/month (45% of total). Annual projected savings: $3,199.20."
